This is related to the CONF-3792 bug I also reported (http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-3792).

When debug is true, the junitreport output displays both the test failure message and the full stack trace. But the first line of the stack trace also contains the failure message. So when the failure message is long (see CONF-3792), it creates messy repetition.

Suggested fix: When debug is true and the failure message is contained in the stack trace output, only display the stack trace output and not the failure message.

