Template-specific markup (i.e. @FOO@) should only be rendered if a template is being displayed. For regular page viewing, it should be ignored.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *Confluence Server*. Using *Confluence Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONFCLOUD-3767].
  {panel}

will require a redesign of the space permissions page....

The following renders as an input field:

{noformat}
@FOO@
{noformat}

The following renders exactly the same as the markup (i.e. the backslashes are still there):

{noformat}
\@FOO\@
{noformat}

Workaround is to use:

{noformat}
&#64;FOO&#64;
{noformat}

